This is a template project to aid in getting started quickly with Java projects.
It uses Gradle as the build system. You will have to make sure that you have Gradle installed
and that it is present in your PATH.

To open the project in IntelliJ IDEA
1. Choose 'Import Project...' from the File menu
2. Select the file build.gradle file in the root of this project
3. Choose all the default options in the next screens.
4. You may have to choose a JDK before you can create the IDEA project. Choose a Java 7 JDK and finish.

To run tests from the command line, type

gradle clean test

You can find test reports under target/test-reports in the root directory of the project
To assemble an executable jar, type

gradle clean installApp

You can find the executable jar for the project in the build/install directory

To run the application, type

gradle run

